, 
<figureCitation id="133B2A2BFFE9EF3C6158FE7CFD45FE2A" box="[626,687,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[196,227,1250,1269]" captionTargetBox="[236,944,194,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-67@10.[236,944,194,1228]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 4. Female reproductive tracts (A, C) and gonocoxa (B, D) of Mecyclothorax spp. A, B. M. flavipes. C, D. M. filipes. Abbreviations: alf, apicolateral fringe setae; am, apicomedial seta; an, apical nematiform setae; bc, bursa copulatrix, co, common oviduct; de, dorsal ensiform seta; dl, dorsal lobe of bursa copulatrix; gc1, basal gonocoxite 1; gc2, apical gonocoxite 2; le, lateral ensiform setae; sg, spermathecal gland; sp, spermatheca; vl, ventral lobe of bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4924364" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4924364/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">4A–B</figureCitation>
